  ${
    $d y ph z $.  $d x y z $.
    tfis.1 $e |- ( x e. On -> ( A. y e. x [ y / x ] ph -> ph ) ) $.
    $( Transfinite Induction Schema.  If all ordinal numbers less than a
       given number ` x ` have a property (induction hypothesis), then all
       ordinal numbers have the property (conclusion).  Exercise 25 of
       [Enderton] p. 200. $)
    tfis $p |- ( x e. On -> ph ) $=
      ( vz cv con0 wcel crab wss wi wral wceq ssrab2 wsbc wa ax-17 hbs1 hbral
